<HEAD>Illinois Van Accident Injures 14</HEAD>
<DATELINE>GODFREY, Ill. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An Easter outing for the disabled ended
with 14 people injured, one critically, when the van they were
riding in swerved off the road near here, struck a tree and burst
into flames.
   The van, from Beverly Farms Foundation Inc., a center for the
developmentally disabled, went off Illinois 267 near Godfrey on
Sunday evening, authorities said.
   Passing motorists stopped and helped passengers from the van
before it burst into flames, said state police Sgt. Lyndall Heyen.
   The van was destroyed by the fire, he said, and traffic on the
highway was blocked for an hour.
   Heyen said the driver lost control of the vehicle because of a
steering problem.
   The critically injured passenger was transferred from Jersey
Community Hospital in Jerseyville to St. Louis University Hospital.
Seven people were in area hospitals, supervisors said. The others
were treated and released.
