<HEAD>16 Mourners Killed in Highway Accident</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BANGKOK, Thailand (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A tractor-trailer knocked a pickup
truck into a canal, killing 16 members of a family en route to
mourn relatives, provincial police said Monday.
   The family was riding in the smaller truck Saturday when the big
rig smashed into their vehicle and sent it plunging into an
irrigation canal 50 miles west of Bangkok, said Police Lt. Saree
Chiemboon.
   Four people in the pickup, including a 4-month-old girl and her
mother, survived.
