<1ST_LINE>r p BC-COLORADOAt-A-Glance     04-04 0285</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-COLORADO At-A-Glance,</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>With AM-Colorado Caucuses</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here, at a glance, are the methods for picking
delegates from Colorado to attend the 1988 Democratic and
Republican national conventions this summer.
</TEXT>
<HEAD>DEMOCRATS</HEAD>
<TEXT>
   Method: Caucus
   Date: Monday, April 4
   Presidential filing deadline: None.
   Pledged delegates: 45
   Super delegates: 6 TOTAL: 51
   Delegates allocated: Monday, April 4
   Selection of delegates: Saturday, April 23 and Saturday, May 21
   
   Colorado Democrats use a four-tiered caucus system for picking
national convention delegates, beginning with precinct caucuses
scheduled for April 4. The precinct caucuses elect delegates to the
county caucuses, which elect delegates to the congressional
district caucuses and to the state convention.
   The congressional district caucuses allocate national convention
delegates proportionally among presidential candidates with one
bonus delegate per district being awarded to the presidential
candidate with the most support in a particular district.
Congressional district caucuses will be held between April 23 and
May 20.
   At-large and party and elected officials delegates will be
allocated according to a presidential preference poll of delegates
to the state convention on May 21.
</TEXT>
<HEAD>REPUBLICANS</HEAD>
<TEXT>
   Method: Caucus
   Date: Monday, April 4
   Presidential filing deadline: None.
   Delegates: 36
   Delegates allocated: Saturday, June 4
   Selection of delegates: Saturday, June 4
   
   Colorado Republicans choose their national convention delegates
through a four-step system of caucuses and conventions, beginning
with the precinct caucuses on April 4.
   The precinct caucuses elect delegates to the county conventions,
which then elect delegates to the congressional district
conventions and the state convention.
   Delegates do not need to state a presidential preference.
   The national convention delegates are chosen at the
congressional district conventions held between May 4 and June 15
and the state convention on June 14.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
