<2ND_LINE>AM-Manufacturing Profits,110</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Manufacturing Profits Down Nearly 25 Percent</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Manufacturing corporations' after-tax profits
averaged 4.3 cents per dollar of sales in the October-December
quarter, down almost one-fourth from the third quarter of 1987, the
government reported Monday.
   The Commerce Department said American manufacturers' after-tax
profits totaled a seasonally adjusted $26.4 billion in the fourth
quarter, compared with $33.6 billion in the third quarter, when
profits averaged 5.6 cents per dollar.
   Sales totaled a seasonally adjusted $609.8 billion in the fourth
quarter compared with $600 billion in the third quarter.
   Both makers of durable goods _ items expected to last three
years _ and non-durable goods saw after-tax earnings decline in the
fourth quarter.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> AP880404-0125 </DOCNO>
<FILEID>AP-NR-04-04-88 2023EDT</FILEID>
<1ST_LINE>r w AM-RuralLoans     04-04 0198</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Rural Loans,190</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>More Rural Development Loans May Go To Areas Of High Unemployment</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   More of the Farmers Home Administration's
rural development loans may be targeted to areas of high
unemployment, the Agriculture Department agency said Monday.
   FmHA administrator Vance L. Clark said a proposed change in the
rules would direct a higher proportion of the agency's business and
industrial loan guarantees to smaller companies where there is high
unemployment.
   The ``B&I'' program involves guarantees by FmHA on loans made by
commercial lenders to provide jobs through new or expanded
businesses in rural areas.
   ``As a general policy, we want to gear the limited B&I loan
funds to smaller businesses in areas where they can provide jobs
for rural people, especially displaced farmers,'' Clark said.
   Under the proposal, loan guarantees would range from 70 percent
to 90 percent of the loan value, with the higher guarantee reserved
for smaller loans.
   A spokesman, Joe O'Neill, said B&I loan guarantees range up to
$10 million per project. Those of up to $2 million would carry the
90 percent guarantee; $2 million to $5 million, 80 percent; and $5
million to $10 million, 70 percent, he said.
</TEXT>
