<1ST_LINE>r i AM-Peru-Guerrillas     04-04 0149</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Peru-Guerrillas,0152</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Guerrillas Kill Two on Bus</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HUANCAYO, Peru (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Guerrillas of the Marxist group Shining
Path dragged the administrator of a large farm and his wife off a
bus and shot them to death, officials reported Monday.
   Police said Mr. and Mrs. Zozino Huaman were killed Sunday
afternoon by three hooded gunmen who stopped a bus belonging to the
farm 42 miles northwest of this state capital, which is 140 miles
east of Lima.
   Eleven other passengers and the driver were with the Huamans on
the bus, the reports said.
   A sign bearing the message ``This is the way traitors die'' and
a drawing of a hammer and sickle was found beside the bodies,
according to police.
   Shining Path began fighting in 1980 and the violence has spread
to most of the country. More than 10,000 non-combatants, rebels,
police, soldiers and public officials have been killed.
</TEXT>
