<HEAD>Opera Company Tenor Charged With Rape</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TORONTO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Mark Christopher DuBois, a tenor with the
Canadian Opera Company, has been charged with sexual assault after
a woman said she was raped at knifepoint by a man who lured her
into his car, police reported.
   Police Sgt. Jim Walsh said the woman, who was not identified,
told police she was standing at a bus stop last week when a car
driver approached and asked for directions. Walsh reported the
driver asked the 21-year-old woman to get into his car and when she
did he drew a knife and sexually assaulted her.
   Walsh said charges have been filed against DuBois, 34.
   ``It's been quite a shock to us,'' said Sara Angelucci,
spokeswoman for the opera company.
   She said DuBois had appeared this year in the company's
production of ``The Merry Widow'' but canceled another scheduled
appearance because of a respiratory illness and exhaustion.
   DuBois made his London debut at Wigmore Hall in 1986 to good
reviews. He has played leading roles with the Canadian Opera
Company and other companies in both Canada and the United States.
