<HEAD>Bus-Truck Collision Kills 19</HEAD>
<DATELINE>RIO DE JANEIRO, Brazil (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The driver of a bus lost control
of the vehicle as it rounded a curve and collided head-on with a
cement truck in an accident that killed 19 people and injured 54,
police reported.
   They said the bus, bound for Belo Horizonte, was carrying 73
people and the accident occurred outside Sete Lagoas, 305 miles
northwest of Rio.
