<HEAD>GARDENING: Tipsy</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   If you have seen birds flying in dizzy patterns late in the fall
it may be from feeding on fermented fruits on trees and shrubs.
They're tipsy.
   Some insects also appear drunk from tippling on fermented juices
of fallen fruit or fermented tree saps. Butterflies and wasps,
ants, flies and perhaps an occasional yellow jacket bee may do
likewise.
</TEXT>
