<1ST_LINE>r f PM-Beard-UP     04-04 0191</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Beard-UP,0199</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Merger Agreement Signed</HEAD>
<DATELINE>OKLAHOMA CITY (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A merger agreement signed between The Beard
Co. of Oklahoma City and Union Pacific Corp. will give Union
Pacific ownership of all outstanding Beard shares in a deal worth
nearly $100 million.
   Union Pacific, which is based in New York, also will acquire the
almost 3.6 million shares of USPCI Inc. that Beard owned. Union
Pacific became a majority owner in January of USPCI, a hazardous
waste management company based in Oklahoma City.
   Beard and Union Pacific announced Friday the merger agreement
had been signed.
   Under terms of the agreement, Beard shareholders will receive
$10 in cash and one share of Beard Oil Co. for each share of The
Beard Co.
   Beard Oil is a wholly owned subsidiary of The Beard Co. Union
Pacific is to provide $85.5 million for payments to Beard
shareholders and to repay company debt. The more than 1 million
shares of Beard owned by Union Pacific will be canceled.
   Another term of the agreement calls for the 375,000 shares of
USPCI now owned by Beard Oil to be purchased by Union Pacific for
$28 per share.
</TEXT>
